cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.COMM, cs.OH, cs.MM

Reasoning: 

1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the performance analysis of different modulation schemes for indoor visible light communication systems, which involves the transmission and processing of information. Therefore, cs.IT is the most likely sub-category for this paper.

2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper deals with the performance evaluation of different modulation schemes for indoor visible light communication systems, which are a part of networking and internet architecture. Hence, cs.NI is also a likely sub-category.

3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking): The paper focuses on the performance comparison of different modulation schemes for indoor visible light communication systems, which are a part of communications and networking. Therefore, cs.COMM is another likely sub-category.

4. cs.OH (Other Computer Science): The paper may also fall under the category of cs.OH as it deals with a specific application of computer science, i.e., visible light communication systems.

5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses the impact of LED nonlinearity on the performance of different modulation schemes for indoor visible light communication systems, which are a part of multimedia applications. Hence, cs.MM is also a possible sub-category.
